18entering the mind\u2019 of Chamizer to identify and decoding his personal associations.\n\nThe prize for solving the riddles increased every day and often amounted to substantial sums of money, thus attracting a large audience. In its seven years on air, the percentage share of listeners increased to 17%,  making him one of the most innovative contributors in radio. Chamizer went on to produce TV game shows, including \"Otzar Hanegev\", \"Yemei Eden BaGalil\", \"Yovel La\u2019Medina\", \"Treasures of One Hundred Years of Zionism\", \"Treasures of World Cup Football\", \"Treasures of Israel at 60\".\n\nHe returned to radio in 2004 with a new game show called The \"Chamizer Sentence\", which offered the highest individual prize awarded in the history of Israeli radio game shows- NIS 240,000. In 2009, Chamizer produced the VOD Treasure for HOT TV, and in 2010, he produced The Treasure of the Century, celebrating 100 years of the Kibbutz Movement in Israel, followed by the New Israel Defense Force Quiz in 2011.\n==Local culture==\nFor decades Chamizer inspired Israelis to connect en-masse with opportunities for informal study via riddles, puzzles, games, nationwide treasure hunts and innovative educational projects. His surname \u2013 Chamizer \u2013 has become synonymous among Israelis with any riddle or intellectual challenge that requires wit, imagination and creativity to solve, and it has entered Hebrew slang as a verb, often conjugated playfully to describe the solving of sophisticated riddles.\n\n== Educational projects ==\n[[File:DanChamizer 23.jpg|150px|thumb|Diploma for completion of Chamizer riddle course]]\nChamizer developed the \"Teaching through Riddles\" educational method, where imaginative-associative riddles characterized by playful wit, wild leaps of imagination and outlandish word association became part of the approved national teaching curriculum in Israeli schools. To date, over half a million students have taken an active part in projects based around Chamizer riddles.\n\nChamizer sees his riddles as tools for encouraging inventive thinking. He explains the purpose of the method as follows: \"The imaginative-associative riddle, like many of life\u2019s problems, has endless solutions. Therefore, finding the correct approach to solving one, offers a perfect simulation for other life challenges that demand a creative input.\"<ref>[http://chidotil.com/p_hidan.php Dan Chamizer explains imaginative riddle in education]</ref>\n\nThe method lends legitimacy to unconventional thinking and unmediated means, stimulating curiosity, creativity, enthusiasm and competitiveness. The coveted cash prize goes to the player who manages to \"enter the riddler\u2019s head,\" but much credit is also given for improvisation, initiative, creative thinking, teamwork, leadership, focus, openness, self-confidence and courage \u2013 and these are the qualities that truly matter. In his words: \"My aim is to instill an alternative way of acquiring study skills and assimilating knowledge.\"\n\nIn 2010, Chamizer established the National Riddle Archive,<ref>[http://chidotil.com/  National Riddles Archive]</ref> a dynamic online database of imaginative-associative riddles) in association with The Kibbutzim College of Education and the Teachers' Union in Israel. Designed to be used as a teaching resource, facilitating both formal and informal learning, the archive is aimed at professional educators and linked to study topics outlined in the national curriculum.\n\nExamples of projects using the \u2018Chamizer education method\u2019:\n*\tAn online project that allows every participating teacher in Israel to select and receive relevant associative riddles with which to engage their pupils (launched 2015).\n*\tAn annual national initiative that motivates school pupils in Israel to recognize \u2013 in a playful, unmediated way \u2013 the importance of lifestyle in fostering a healthy heart (Hebrew and Arabic). \n*\tA  Haifa-based educational initiative, not only connecting pupils and parents to their own neighborhoods and communities, but also illuminating their shared past and introducing them to other educational establishments in their area (launched 2015, in Hebrew and Arabic) \n*\tA two-year nationwide project intended to facilitate an understanding of the legacy of Israel's former leaders among Israeli schoolchildren (launched 2013)<ref>[http://www.frixell.net/leaders/ Israel Leaders Legacy] 2015.</ref> \n*\tA national project aimed at promoting opportunities for greater exposure to the culture and heritage of Ethiopian Jewry among the wider school population in Israel.<ref>[http://www.frixell.net/ethiopia/  Discovering \"Et Yof Ya\" - her beauti]</ref>\n*\tA project examining, defining, and promoting the legacy of the [[Israeli Labor Party]], its philosophy and its leaders. (launched 2012, in association with Beit Berl Education College and the Knesset) \n*\tAn innovative makeover for the classic IDF (Israel Defense Force) quiz, designed to give every soldier the opportunity to demonstrate their knowledge of the force's core values, its national heritage and its position on environmental issues (launched 2010)\n*\tMonopoly-like interactive game, created for the Ministry of Education, emphasizing the importance of the Hebrew language and its correct usage (launched 2009).<ref>[http://www.frixell.net/ivrit/  Hebrew Language Enhancement in the Educational System]</ref>\n*\tAn interactive game designed for the benefit of school children in Eilat, teaching them about the city's heritage and history (launched 2013-15)<ref>[http://www.frixell.net/eilat/ The History of Eilat]</ref>\n*\tAn interactive game designed to help Israeli high school pupils assimilate curriculum content in Sociology (launched 2013-15)<ref>[http://www.frixell.net/socio/    Sociology students in Israel]</ref>\n*\tNationwide educational game, in association with the Israeli Ministry of Education, connecting Israeli children with immigration centers around the country, and facilitating a better understanding of the importance of successfully integrating immigrant children into society (launched 2016)\n\nA long-standing environmental activist, Chamizer produced a series of games designed to promote environmental awareness,  highlighting harm done to the countryside by Israeli citizens and the importance of confronting profit-seeking power brokers.\n\n==Art career==\nChamizer is a conceptual artist who creates environmental sculptures. \n<gallery>\nFile:DanChamizer 03.jpg| \u201cI have no other country\u201d \u2013 Artists\u2019 Gallery, Ein Hod.\nFile:PikiWiki Israel 13673 Truth or Nothing by Dan Chamizer in Ein Hod.jpg|Truth or Nothing by Dan Chamizer in Ein Hod.\nFile:PikiWiki Israel 13672 Happy Glasses by Dan Chamizer.jpg|Happy Glasses of Itche Ein hod\nFile:DanChamizer 04.jpg| \u201cOh, my country\u201d \u2013 Janco Dada Museom, Ein Hod.\nFile:DanChamizer 14.jpg|The riddle of Tel Aviv.\nFile:PikiWiki Israel 13674 End of the Days Mail by Dan Chamizer in Ein Hod.jpg|The end of days mail boxes\"  Ein Hod.\nFile:PB130043.JPG|\u201cThe Mediterranean sea\u201d \u2013 Street Art, [[Haifa]].\nFile:DanChamizer 18.jpg|\u201cThe state of the nation\u201d  Ein Hod 2001.\nFile:DanChamizer 13.jpg|\u201cAzulai the cop\u201d\u2013 Street Art, Ein Hod.\nFile:DanChamizer 11.jpg|Table Football Playbox, Street Art, Ein Hod.\n</gallery>\n==Published works==\n===Books===\n*\tChamizer's book of riddles: From the mechanized Italian to the Iraqi finger (Keter, 1992)\n*\tPanta Rei: Casualties in Grandma's trunk (Zmorah Bitan, 1998) \u2013 a biographical evocation of Chamizer's father, Emmanuel.<ref>[http://www.tiktakti.co.il/catalog/kip/chamizer/panta-rhei/ Panta-Rei -Casualties in Grandma\u2019s trunk]</ref>\n\n'''Children's books''':\n*\tChidani in the animal kingdom (Matar, 2009)\n*\tChidani meets friends<ref>[http://www.booknet.co.il/prodtxt.asp?id=51677#.WetkN2ZryUk Booknet]</ref> (Matar, 2010)\n*\tChidani protects the environment (Matar, 2011)\n\n===Poetry===\n*\t\"Closed Formation\" (1993 ) \u2013 includes poems by Chamizer's friend and fellow Arkia pilot, Trigg Messing (1923\u201389)<ref>[http://www.tiktakti.co.il/catalog/kip/chamizer/mivne/#p=I Close Formation - flying to combat]</ref>\n*\tCrash landing (1997 ) \u2013 Some of the poems from this book were composed and released on record by Dudu Elharar (1998).<ref>[https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=xhP43e4kRfo Crash Landing 1997]</ref>\n*\tEshet (2008)\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n*\tList of publications by Chamizer, in the National Library catalogue\n*\tChamizer's internet website \u2013 [http://www.chamizer.com Chamizer.com]\n*\tCheruti-Sober, [https://www.themarker.com/career/1.1693827 Tali, The biggest mystery of all: how much money does Chamizer make from his riddles?] in The Marker, 25 April 2012\n*\tZorea, Chen, [http://www.nrg.co.il/online/54/ART2/409/292.html The orthodox demolish Zionism: eye to eye with Dan Chamizer], nrg website, 17 October 2012\n*\tAharon Barnea [https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=8rCbwlHM9-o Interview with Dan Chamizer] in the radio programme \"Those were the days\" on the Knesset Channel, YouTube, 27 July 2016\n*\tCheruti-Sober, Tali, [https://www.themarker.com/career/1.3917264 Our Airforce friends trod over our bodies], The Marker, 9 March 2017\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Chamizer, Dan}}\n[[Category:1947 births]]\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:Israeli aviators]]\n[[Category:Israeli environmentalists]]\n[[Category:Israeli Jews]]\n[[Category:Israeli writers]]\n[[Category:Israeli artists]]\n[[Category:Israeli Air Force personnel]]\n[[Category:Puzzle designers]]\n[[Category:Tel Aviv University alumni]]\n", "name_user": "Ser Amantio di Nicolao", "label": "safe", "comment": "add authority control", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Dan_Chamizer"}
{"title_page": "James Linton (hacker)", "text_new": "{{short description|Email prankster}}\n{{Infobox person\n|name        = James Linton\n|image       = \n|caption     = \n| birth_date    = \n|birth_place = \n|other_names = SINON_REBORN\n|known_for   = Email pranks\n|occupation  = Email threat researcher\n|nationality = British\n}}\n'''James Linton''' is a [[social engineering|social engineer]] and email [[Prank call|prankster]] known for duping high profile celebrities and politicians. For five months in 2016 through to 2017, the \"lazy anarchist\"<ref>{{cite news |last1=Schlagenhauf |first1=Wes |title=One of the best online pranksters of all time is hanging up his keyboard |url=https://thehustle.co/one-best-online-pranksters-time-hanging-keyboard/ |accessdate=10 April 2020 |date=8 November 2017}}</ref> known by the [[Twitter]] alias '''SINON_REBORN''' created over 150 look-alike email accounts and emailed high-profile individuals in the political, financial, and entertainment industries.\n== Background ==\nLinton is a former [[Web developer|web developer]]. He was suspended from his job when his bosses suspected he was emailing victims at work.<ref name=\"buzzfeed\">{{cite news |last1=Mac |first1=Ryan |title=This Man Pranked Eric Trump And Harvey Weinstein \u2014 Now He Just Wants A Job |url=https://www.buzzfeednews.com/article/ryanmac/the-email-prankster-sinon-reborn-is-calling-it-quits |accessdate=10 April 2020 |date=7 November 2017}}</ref> He lives in [[Manchester]] [[United Kingdom|UK]] with his partner and three cats.<ref>{{cite news |last1=Jeffries |first1=Adrianne |title=How to prank the rich and powerful without really trying |url=https://theoutline.com/post/2059/how-to-prank-the-rich-and-powerful-without-really-trying?zd=1&zi=qbqck7z7 |accessdate=10 April 2020 |date=4 August 2017}}</ref>\n\nHis moniker SINON_REBORN comes from [[Sinon]], the name of the Greek Soldier who persuades the Trojans to accept the [[Trojan Horse]], basis of the [[Trojan horse (computing)|eponymous computing trick]] he utilised.<ref name=\"wired\" />\n\nHe revealed his identity to the media in September 2017 and later became a threat researcher for email security firm Agari.<ref name=\"nri\" />\n\n== Prank Spree ==\nLinton's first prank was targeting far-right media pundit [[Ann Coulter]], posing as [[David Clarke (sheriff)|Sheriff David Clarke]] persuading her to review an article about immigration.<ref>{{cite news |last1=Braue |first1=David |title=If Scott Morrison emails you, check the header |url=https://ia.acs.org.au/article/2019/if-scott-morrison-emails-you--check-the-header.html |accessdate=10 April 2020 |date=20 September 2019}}</ref>\n\nIn May 2017, Linton began his spree with, [[Jes Staley]], CEO of [[Barclays]] as businessman [[John McFarlane]], pranked with an [[acrostic]] alluding to [[whistleblower]] investigation.<ref>{{cite news |last1=Treanor |first1=Jill |title=Barclays boss Jes Staley fooled into email exchange with prankster |url=https://www.theguardian.com/business/2017/may/11/barclays-boss-jes-staley-fooled-into-email-exchange-with-prankster-not-john-mcfarlane |accessdate=10 April 2020 |date=12 May 2017}}</ref> Days later, he elicited sexist remarks from [[Mark Carney]], [[Governor of the Bank of England]] and an invitation to a fake soiree.<ref>{{cite news |last1=Allen |first1=Katie |title=Bank of England governor falls for email prank but maintains his composure |url=https://www.theguardian.com/business/2017/may/23/bank-of-england-governor-falls-for-email-prank-but-maintains-his-composure |accessdate=10 April 2020 |date=23 May 2017}}</ref> In June, impersonating [[Jeremy Corbyn]]'s press secretary,  British politician [[Diane Abbott]] was tricked into commenting about her health.<ref>{{cite news |last1=Hughes |first1=Laura |title=Diane Abbott appears to fall victim to a hoax email conversation with online prankster |url=https://www.telegraph.co.uk/news/2017/06/06/diane-abbott-appears-fall-victim-hoax-email-conversation-online/ |accessdate=6 April 2020 |date=6 June 2017}}</ref>\n\nShortly after, he tricked [[Lloyd Blankfein]], CEO of [[Goldman Sachs]] into making a dig a president Trump, [[Citigroup]] banking chiefs [[Michael Corbat]] and Stephen Bird  with links to his previous pranks<ref>{{cite news |last1=Sonenshine |first1=Jacob |title=Goldman CEO gets duped by email prankster |url=https://nypost.com/2017/06/12/goldman-ceo-gets-duped-by-email-prankster/ |accessdate=10 April 2020 |date=12 June 2017}}</ref> then and corresponded with [[James P. Gorman|James Gorman]], CEO of [[Morgan Stanley]] with a story about catching a salmon.<ref>{{cite news |last1=English |first1=Carleton |title=Morgan Stanley CEO James Gorman falls for email prank |url=https://nypost.com/2017/06/14/morgan-stanley-ceo-james-gorman-falls-for-email-prank/ |accessdate=10 April 2020 |date=14 June 2017}}</ref>\n\nIn late June, right-wing media personality [[Katie Hopkins]], was tricked into joining a fictional TV show \"Adders Basket\" debating feminists, liberals and vegans.<ref name=\"nri\">{{cite news |last1=Scammell |first1=Robert |title=Linton Reborn  How the Email Prankster Became a Cyber Crimefighter |url=https://verdict-encrypt.nridigital.com/verdict_encrypt_summer_2019/linton_reborn_how_the_email_prankster_became_a_cyber_crimefighter |accessdate=6 April 2020}}</ref>\n\nIn August, he targeted the [[White House]]. Posing as [[Jared Kushner]] he tricked a senior cyber security advisor into his authenticity, taunted then media chief [[Anthony Scaramucci]] as ex chief of staff [[Reince Priebus]] just before he was fired,<ref>{{cite news |last1=Booth |first1=Robert |title=Prankster says he targeted Scaramucci over mental health insult |url=https://www.theguardian.com/technology/2017/aug/01/prankster-says-he-targeted-scaramucci-over-mental-health-insult |accessdate=10 April 2020 |date=1 August 2017}}</ref> as [[Jon Huntsman Jr.|Jon Huntsman]], invited US Homeland Security Advisor [[Tom Bossert]] to a soiree, and joked with [[Eric Trump]] about his dad's similarities to [[Vladimir Putin|Putin]].<ref>{{cite news |last1=Tapper |first1=Jake |title=White House officials tricked by email prankster |url=https://edition.cnn.com/2017/07/31/politics/white-house-officials-tricked-by-email-prankster/index.html |accessdate=10 April 2020 |date=1 August 2017}}</ref> Personal lawyer to Donald Trump [[Michael Cohen (lawyer)|Michael Cohen]] was persudes to tweet a photograph<ref name=\"buzzfeed\" /> and [[Jared Kushner]]'s lawyer [[Abbe Lowell]] incorrectly forwarded a request from the [[United States Senate Select Committee on Intelligence|senate intelligence committee]] asking about Kushner's undisclosed private email account to a fake account.<ref>{{cite news |last1=Farhi |first1=Paul |title=Email hoax comes back to haunt Jared Kushner\u2019s attorney |url=https://www.washingtonpost.com/lifestyle/style/email-hoax-comes-back-to-haunt-jared-kushners-attorney/2017/09/28/c2df2c4a-a490-11e7-ade1-76d061d56efa_story.html |accessdate=10 April 2020 |date=28 September 2017}}</ref><ref>{{cite news |last1=Zambis |first1=John |title=Jared Kushner Didn't Disclose Personal Email Account To Senate Committee |url=https://mavenroundtable.io/theintellectualist/science/jared-kushner-didn-t-disclose-personal-email-account-to-senate-committee-Xyjb1YbX80qJvIR2a7Dccw |accessdate=10 April 2020 |date=31 October 2017}}</ref> Lawyer [[Ty Cobb (attorney)|Ty Cobb]] and press secretary [[Sarah Sanders]] corresponded, joking about [[Drone strike|droning]] journalist [[Natasha Bertrand]].<ref>{{cite news |last1=Bertrand |first1=Natasha |title=Trump lawyer Ty Cobb, fooled by 'email prankster,' asks for 'drone' in private emails slamming reporter |url=https://www.businessinsider.com/ty-cobb-emails-prankster-drone-reporter-2017-9?r=US&IR=T |accessdate=10 April 2020 |date=7 September 2017}}</ref>\n\nIn early August, former UK [[Home Secretary]] [[Amber Rudd]] briefly corresponded from her personal address about upcoming announcements to a fake advisor account.<ref name=\"wired\">{{cite news |last1=Stokel-Walker |first1=Chris |title=Revealed: The real identity of prankster king SINON_REBORN |url=https://www.wired.co.uk/article/the-true-story-of-sinon-reborn-2017s-greatest-prankster |accessdate=6 April 2020 |date=28 September 2017}}</ref><ref>{{cite news |last1=Booth |first1=Robert |title=Amber Rudd latest to fall victim to email hoaxer using fake account |url=https://www.theguardian.com/politics/2017/aug/09/amber-rudd-latest-to-fall-victim-to-email-hoaxer-using-fake-account |accessdate=10 April 2020 |date=9 August 2017}}</ref>\n\nLater in August, [[Breitbart News|Breitbart]] editors [[Alex Marlow]] and [[Joel Pollak]] commented they would do [[Steve Bannon]]'s 'dirty work' to fake a Steve Bannon account, ousting [[Jared Kushner]] and [[Ivanka Trump]] and shared a personal smear about their private lives.<ref>{{cite news |last1=Darcy |first1=Oliver |title=Emails: Breitbart editor pledges to do 'dirty work' for Bannon, smears Ivanka |url=https://money.cnn.com/2017/08/22/media/breitbart-prank-emails/index.html |accessdate=10 April 2020 |date=22 August 2017}}</ref>\n\nIn September, laywer [[Jamie Gorelick]] briefly fell for fake emails from her client Jared Kushner but didn't reveal anything confidential.<ref>{{cite news |last1=Rubino |first1=Kathryn |title=It Happened AGAIN \u2014 Another Biglaw Partner Falls For Internet Prank |url=https://abovethelaw.com/2017/10/it-happened-again-another-biglaw-partner-falls-for-internet-prank/ |accessdate=10 April 2020 |date=5 October 2017}}</ref>\n\nIn October, Linton posted as now disgraced Hollywood Producer [[Harvey Weinstein]], confessing regrets for his actions to his former lawyers  [[Lanny Davis]] and [[Lisa Bloom]].<ref>{{cite news |last1=Digg Team |title=Email Prankster Strikes Again, Fooling Harvey Weinstein And His Legal Team |url=https://digg.com/2017/harvey-weinstein-lisa-bloom-email-prankster |accessdate=10 April 2020 |date=10 October 2017}}</ref>\n\nLater in October, he targeted [[Shark Tank]] personality [[Robert Herjavec]] as the company CEO, inviting him to a toga party. Later the fake account was copied into official financial projection documents.<ref name=\"buzzfeed\" />\n\nFinally in late October, UK [[National Cyber Security Centre (United Kingdom)|National Cyber Security Centre]] technical director Ian Levy was targeted with a fake industry event, however Levy correctly identified the unexpected headers.<ref>{{cite news |last1=Levy |first1=Ian |title=The serious side of pranking |url=https://www.ncsc.gov.uk/blog-post/serious-side-pranking |accessdate=6 April 2020 |date=30 October 2017}}</ref>\n\n== Other pranks ==\n* [[Kevin Spacey]], American actor, producer, and singer\n* Alan Stewart, CFO [[Tesco]] as [[John Allan (businessman)|John Allan]], CEO Tesco\n* [[Dennis Muilenburg]], CEO, [[Boeing]] as [[Ed Liddy]], Board Member of Boeing\n* [[Norman Tebbit]], UK Politician as [[Boris Johnson]], then Secretary of State for Foreign Affairs. Fake Johnson told Tebbit to \"go fuck yourself\".<ref>{{cite news |last1=Gray |first1=Jasmin |title=Anthony Scaramucci Sent Some Seriously Bizarre Emails To A Prankster Pretending To Be Reince Priebus |url=https://www.huffingtonpost.co.uk/entry/anthony-scaramucci-emails-prankster-pretending-reince-priebus_uk_59803a43e4b00bb8ff393655?guccounter=1&guce_referrer=aHR0cHM6Ly93d3cuZ29vZ2xlLmNvbS8&guce_referrer_sig=AQAAABWxAJdRPEx5U6LWSe7EylppVsWv2paMsz6yDJ4fYWcmQGO7M2gCP-tchRnnlSdQYM1fElRm_wuAimXwDH38Yfj5h1jZvs-cAGxkbcVelJXkBzZBWbpUZbowB5kGNii5jAZSeRZ3arT_zratqmgS_t_N79N6DZ5k12-Oh2YXBYgI |accessdate=10 April 2020 |date=1 August 2017}}</ref>\n* Jessica Shears, UK [[Love Island]] reality TV star\n* [[James Woods]] Hollywood actor and producer\n* [[Ezra Levant]], CEO of [[Rebel Media]]\n* [[Tucker Carlson]] and [[Brian Kilmeade]] of [[Fox News]]<ref>{{cite web |title=Email Prankter\u2122 |url=http://www.emailprankster.com/ |accessdate=10 April 2020}}</ref>\n\n== External links ==\n* [http://www.emailprankster.com/ emailprankster.com] - Personal site\n\n== References ==\n[[Category:Writers about computer security]]\n[[Category:People associated with computer security]]\n[[Category:British computer specialists]]\n[[Category:Hacking (computer security)]]\n[[Category:Hacking in the 2010s]]\n[[Category:Living people]]\n", "text_old": "{{short description|Email prankster}}\n{{Infobox person\n|name        = James Linton\n|image       = \n|caption     = \n| birth_date    = \n|birth_place = \n|other_names = SINON_REBORN\n|known_for   = Email pranks\n|occupation  = Email threat researcher\n|nationality = British\n}}\n'''James Linton''' is a [[social engineering|social engineer]] and email [[Prank call|prankster]] known for duping high profile celebrities and politicians. For five months in 2016 through to 2017, the \"lazy anarchist\"<ref>{{cite news |last1=Schlagenhauf |first1=Wes |title=One of the best online pranksters of all time is hanging up his keyboard |url=https://thehustle.co/one-best-online-pranksters-time-hanging-keyboard/ |accessdate=10 April 2020 |date=8 November 2017}}</ref> known by the [[Twitter]] alias '''SINON_REBORN''' created over 150 look-alike email accounts and emailed high-profile individuals in the political, financial, and entertainment industries.\n== Background ==\nLinton is a former [[Web developer|web developer]]. He was suspended from his job when his bosses suspected he was emailing victims at work.<ref name=\"buzzfeed\">{{cite news |last1=Mac |first1=Ryan |title=This Man Pranked Eric Trump And Harvey Weinstein \u2014 Now He Just Wants A Job |url=https://www.buzzfeednews.com/article/ryanmac/the-email-prankster-sinon-reborn-is-calling-it-quits |accessdate=10 April 2020 |date=7 November 2017}}</ref> He lives in [[Manchester]] [[United Kingdom|UK]] with his partner and three cats.<ref>{{cite news |last1=Jeffries |first1=Adrianne |title=How to prank the rich and powerful without really trying |url=https://theoutline.com/post/2059/how-to-prank-the-rich-and-powerful-without-really-trying?zd=1&zi=qbqck7z7 |accessdate=10 April 2020 |date=4 August 2017}}</ref>\n\nHis moniker SINON_REBORN comes from [[Sinon]], the name of the Greek Soldier who persuades the Trojans to accept the [[Trojan Horse]], basis of the [[Trojan horse (computing)|eponymous computing trick]] he utilised.<ref name=\"wired\" />\n\nHe revealed his identity to the media in September 2017 and later became a threat researcher for email security firm Agari.<ref name=\"nri\" />\n\n== Prank Spree ==\nLinton's first prank was targeting far-right media pundit [[Ann Coulter]], posing as [[David Clarke (sheriff)|Sheriff David Clarke]] persuading her to review an article about immigration.<ref>{{cite news |last1=Braue |first1=David |title=If Scott Morrison emails you, check the header |url=https://ia.acs.org.au/article/2019/if-scott-morrison-emails-you--check-the-header.html |accessdate=10 April 2020 |date=20 September 2019}}</ref>\n\nIn May 2017, Linton began his spree with, [[Jes Staley]], CEO of [[Barclays]] as businessman [[John McFarlane]], pranked with an [[acrostic]] alluding to [[whistleblower]] investigation.<ref>{{cite news |last1=Treanor |first1=Jill |title=Barclays boss Jes Staley fooled into email exchange with prankster |url=https://www.theguardian.com/business/2017/may/11/barclays-boss-jes-staley-fooled-into-email-exchange-with-prankster-not-john-mcfarlane |accessdate=10 April 2020 |date=12 May 2017}}</ref> Days later, he elicited sexist remarks from [[Mark Carney]], [[Governor of the Bank of England]] and an invitation to a fake soiree.<ref>{{cite news |last1=Allen |first1=Katie |title=Bank of England governor falls for email prank but maintains his composure |url=https://www.theguardian.com/business/2017/may/23/bank-of-england-governor-falls-for-email-prank-but-maintains-his-composure |accessdate=10 April 2020 |date=23 May 2017}}</ref> In June, impersonating [[Jeremy Corbyn]]'s press secretary,  British politician [[Diane Abbott]] was tricked into commenting about her health.<ref>{{cite news |last1=Hughes |first1=Laura |title=Diane Abbott appears to fall victim to a hoax email conversation with online prankster |url=https://www.telegraph.co.uk/news/2017/06/06/diane-abbott-appears-fall-victim-hoax-email-conversation-online/ |accessdate=6 April 2020 |date=6 June 2017}}</ref>\n\nShortly after, he tricked [[Lloyd Blankfein]], CEO of [[Goldman Sachs]] into making a dig a president Trump, [[Citigroup]] banking chiefs [[Michael Corbat]] and Stephen Bird  with links to his previous pranks<ref>{{cite news |last1=Sonenshine |first1=Jacob |title=Goldman CEO gets duped by email prankster |url=https://nypost.com/2017/06/12/goldman-ceo-gets-duped-by-email-prankster/ |accessdate=10 April 2020 |date=12 June 2017}}</ref> then and corresponded with [[James P. Gorman|James Gorman]], CEO of [[Morgan Stanley]] with a story about catching a salmon.<ref>{{cite news |last1=English |first1=Carleton |title=Morgan Stanley CEO James Gorman falls for email prank |url=https://nypost.com/2017/06/14/morgan-stanley-ceo-james-gorman-falls-for-email-prank/ |accessdate=10 April 2020 |date=14 June 2017}}</ref>\n\nIn late June, right-wing media personality [[Katie Hopkins]], was tricked into joining a fictional TV show \"Adders Basket\" debating feminists, liberals and vegans.<ref name=\"nri\">{{cite news |last1=Scammell |first1=Robert |title=Linton Reborn  How the Email Prankster Became a Cyber Crimefighter |url=https://verdict-encrypt.nridigital.com/verdict_encrypt_summer_2019/linton_reborn_how_the_email_prankster_became_a_cyber_crimefighter |accessdate=6 April 2020}}</ref>\n\nIn August, he targeted the [[White House]]. Posing as [[Jared Kushner]] he tricked a senior cyber security advisor into his authenticity, taunted then media chief [[Anthony Scaramucci]] as ex chief of staff [[Reince Priebus]] just before he was fired,<ref>{{cite news |last1=Booth |first1=Robert |title=Prankster says he targeted Scaramucci over mental health insult |url=https://www.theguardian.com/technology/2017/aug/01/prankster-says-he-targeted-scaramucci-over-mental-health-insult |accessdate=10 April 2020 |date=1 August 2017}}</ref> as [[Jon Huntsman Jr.|Jon Huntsman]], invited US Homeland Security Advisor [[Tom Bossert]] to a soiree, and joked with [[Eric Trump]] about his dad's similarities to [[Vladimir Putin|Putin]].<ref>{{cite news |last1=Tapper |first1=Jake |title=White House officials tricked by email prankster |url=https://edition.cnn.com/2017/07/31/politics/white-house-officials-tricked-by-email-prankster/index.html |accessdate=10 April 2020 |date=1 August 2017}}</ref> Personal lawyer to Donald Trump [[Michael Cohen (lawyer)|Michael Cohen]] was persudes to tweet a photograph<ref name=\"buzzfeed\" /> and [[Jared Kushner]]'s lawyer [[Abbe Lowell]] incorrectly forwarded a request from the [[United States Senate Select Committee on Intelligence|senate intelligence committee]] asking about Kushner's undisclosed private email account to a fake account.<ref>{{cite news |last1=Farhi |first1=Paul |title=Email hoax comes back to haunt Jared Kushner\u2019s attorney |url=https://www.washingtonpost.com/lifestyle/style/email-hoax-comes-back-to-haunt-jared-kushners-attorney/2017/09/28/c2df2c4a-a490-11e7-ade1-76d061d56efa_story.html |accessdate=10 April 2020 |date=28 September 2017}}</ref><ref>{{cite news |last1=Zambis |first1=John |title=Jared Kushner Didn't Disclose Personal Email Account To Senate Committee |url=https://mavenroundtable.io/theintellectualist/science/jared-kushner-didn-t-disclose-personal-email-account-to-senate-committee-Xyjb1YbX80qJvIR2a7Dccw |accessdate=10 April 2020 |date=31 October 2017}}</ref> Lawyer [[Ty Cobb (attorney)|Ty Cobb]] and press secretary [[Sarah Sanders]] corresponding, joking about [[Drone strike|droning]] journalist [[Natasha Bertrand]].<ref>{{cite news |last1=Bertrand |first1=Natasha |title=Trump lawyer Ty Cobb, fooled by 'email prankster,' asks for 'drone' in private emails slamming reporter |url=https://www.businessinsider.com/ty-cobb-emails-prankster-drone-reporter-2017-9?r=US&IR=T |accessdate=10 April 2020 |date=7 September 2017}}</ref>\n\nIn early August, former UK [[Home Secretary]] [[Amber Rudd]] briefly corresponded from her personal address about upcoming announcements to a fake advisor account.<ref name=\"wired\">{{cite news |last1=Stokel-Walker |first1=Chris |title=Revealed: The real identity of prankster king SINON_REBORN |url=https://www.wired.co.uk/article/the-true-story-of-sinon-reborn-2017s-greatest-prankster |accessdate=6 April 2020 |date=28 September 2017}}</ref><ref>{{cite news |last1=Booth |first1=Robert |title=Amber Rudd latest to fall victim to email hoaxer using fake account |url=https://www.theguardian.com/politics/2017/aug/09/amber-rudd-latest-to-fall-victim-to-email-hoaxer-using-fake-account |accessdate=10 April 2020 |date=9 August 2017}}</ref>\n\nLater in August, [[Breitbart News|Breitbart]] editors [[Alex Marlow]] and [[Joel Pollak]] commented they would do [[Steve Bannon]]'s 'dirty work' to fake a Steve Bannon account, ousting [[Jared Kushner]] and [[Ivanka Trump]] and shared a personal smear about their private lives.<ref>{{cite news |last1=Darcy |first1=Oliver |title=Emails: Breitbart editor pledges to do 'dirty work' for Bannon, smears Ivanka |url=https://money.cnn.com/2017/08/22/media/breitbart-prank-emails/index.html |accessdate=10 April 2020 |date=22 August 2017}}</ref>\n\nIn September, laywer [[Jamie Gorelick]] briefly fell for fake emails from her client Jared Kushner but didn't reveal anything confidential.<ref>{{cite news |last1=Rubino |first1=Kathryn |title=It Happened AGAIN \u2014 Another Biglaw Partner Falls For Internet Prank |url=https://abovethelaw.com/2017/10/it-happened-again-another-biglaw-partner-falls-for-internet-prank/ |accessdate=10 April 2020 |date=5 October 2017}}</ref>\n\nIn October, Linton posted as now disgraced Hollywood Producer [[Harvey Weinstein]], confessing regrets for his actions to his former lawyers  [[Lanny Davis]] and [[Lisa Bloom]].<ref>{{cite news |last1=Digg Team |title=Email Prankster Strikes Again, Fooling Harvey Weinstein And His Legal Team |url=https://digg.com/2017/harvey-weinstein-lisa-bloom-email-prankster |accessdate=10 April 2020 |date=10 October 2017}}</ref>\n\nLater in October, he targeted [[Shark Tank]] personality [[Robert Herjavec]] as the company CEO, inviting him to a toga party. Later the fake account was copied into official financial projection documents.<ref name=\"buzzfeed\" />\n\nFinally in late October, UK [[National Cyber Security Centre (United Kingdom)|National Cyber Security Centre]] technical director Ian Levy was targeted with a fake industry event, however Levy correctly identified the unexpected headers.<ref>{{cite news |last1=Levy |first1=Ian |title=The serious side of pranking |url=https://www.ncsc.gov.uk/blog-post/serious-side-pranking |accessdate=6 April 2020 |date=30 October 2017}}</ref>\n\n== Other pranks ==\n* [[Kevin Spacey]], American actor, producer, and singer\n* Alan Stewart, CFO [[Tesco]] as [[John Allan (businessman)|John Allan]], CEO Tesco\n* [[Dennis Muilenburg]], CEO, [[Boeing]] as [[Ed Liddy]], Board Member of Boeing\n* [[Norman Tebbit]], UK Politician as [[Boris Johnson]], then Secretary of State for Foreign Affairs. Fake Johnson told Tebbit to \"go fuck yourself\".<ref>{{cite news |last1=Gray |first1=Jasmin |title=Anthony Scaramucci Sent Some Seriously Bizarre Emails To A Prankster Pretending To Be Reince Priebus |url=https://www.huffingtonpost.co.uk/entry/anthony-scaramucci-emails-prankster-pretending-reince-priebus_uk_59803a43e4b00bb8ff393655?guccounter=1&guce_referrer=aHR0cHM6Ly93d3cuZ29vZ2xlLmNvbS8&guce_referrer_sig=AQAAABWxAJdRPEx5U6LWSe7EylppVsWv2paMsz6yDJ4fYWcmQGO7M2gCP-tchRnnlSdQYM1fElRm_wuAimXwDH38Yfj5h1jZvs-cAGxkbcVelJXkBzZBWbpUZbowB5kGNii5jAZSeRZ3arT_zratqmgS_t_N79N6DZ5k12-Oh2YXBYgI |accessdate=10 April 2020 |date=1 August 2017}}</ref>\n* Jessica Shears, UK [[Love Island]] reality TV star\n* [[James Woods]] Hollywood actor and producer\n* [[Ezra Levant]], CEO of [[Rebel Media]]\n* [[Tucker Carlson]] and [[Brian Kilmeade]] of [[Fox News]]<ref>{{cite web |title=Email Prankter\u2122 |url=http://www.emailprankster.com/ |accessdate=10 April 2020}}</ref>\n\n== External links ==\n* [http://www.emailprankster.com/ emailprankster.com] - Personal site\n\n== References ==\n[[Category:Writers about computer security]]\n[[Category:People associated with computer security]]\n[[Category:British computer specialists]]\n[[Category:Hacking (computer security)]]\n[[Category:Hacking in the 2010s]]\n[[Category:Living people]]\n", "name_user": "Deku-shrub", "label": "safe", "comment": "\u2192\u200ePrank Spree", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/James_Linton_(hacker)"}
