rd pass to retake the lead 20\u201317. Though, the Niners ended up winning the game when Jimmy Garoppolo found Dante Pettis on a 5-yard pass for a final score of 24\u201320.\n\nWith the loss, the Steelers fell to 0\u20133 for the first time since 2013.\n\n====Week 4: vs. Cincinnati Bengals====\n{{Americanfootballbox\n|titlestyle={{NFLPrimaryStyle|Pittsburgh Steelers|year=2019|border=2}};text-align:center;\n|state=autocollapse\n|title=Week Four: Cincinnati Bengals at Pittsburgh Steelers&nbsp;\u2013 Game summary\n|date={{dow tooltip|September 30, 2019}}\n|time=8:15&nbsp;p.m. EDT\n|road=Bengals\n|R1=3|R2=0|R3=0|R4=0\n|home='''Steelers'''\n|H1=0|H2=10|H3=14|H4=3\n|stadium=Heinz Field, Pittsburgh, Pennsylvania\n|attendance=57,959\n|weather=Clear, {{convert|76|F|C}}\n|referee=[[Bill Vinovich]]\n|TV=[[Monday Night Football|ESPN]]\n|TVAnnouncers=[[Joe Tessitore]], [[Booger McFarland]], [[Lisa Salters]] and [[John Parry (American football official)|John Parry]]\n|reference=[https://www.nfl.com/gamecenter/2019093000/2019/REG4/bengals@steelers Recap], [https://nflcdns.nfl.com/liveupdate/gamecenter/57962/PIT_Gamebook.pdf Game Book]\n|scoring=\n'''First quarter'''\n*CIN \u2013 [[Randy Bullock]] 28-yard field goal, 8:22. ''Bengals 3\u20130. '''Drive: 4 plays, 5 yards, 0:54.'''''\n'''Second quarter'''\n*PIT \u2013 [[James Conner (American football)|James Conner]] 21-yard pass from [[Mason Rudolph (American football)|Mason Rudolph]] ([[Chris Boswell]] kick), 10:32. ''Steelers 7\u20133. '''Drive: 5 plays, 46 yards, 2:40.'''''\n*PIT \u2013 Chris Boswell 29-yard field goal, 0:58. ''Steelers 10\u20133. '''Drive: 11 plays, 60 yards, 4:51.'''''\n'''Third quarter'''\n*PIT \u2013 [[Jaylen Samuels]] 2-yard run (Chris Boswell kick), 10:36. ''Steelers 17\u20133. '''Drive: 8 plays, 75 yards, 4:24.'''''\n*PIT \u2013 [[Diontae Johnson]] 43-yard pass from Mason Rudolph (Chris Boswell kick), 9:24. ''Steelers 24\u20133. '''Drive: 2 plays, 43 yards, 0:11.'''''\n'''Fourth quarter'''\n*PIT \u2013 Chri